ERROR #4 - PORT Conflicts: EADDRINUSE on 6000 and 7000
================================================================================

Observed behavior:
- npm start failed with:
  Error: listen EADDRINUSE: address already in use :::6000
  Then: Error: listen EADDRINUSE: address already in use :::7000

Root causes:
1. PORT environment variable changed from 4000 to 7000 to 6000
2. Port 7000 occupied by macOS ControlCenter system service
3. Port 6000 occupied by stale Node process

Solution:
1. Changed PORT in .env back to 4000
2. Killed stale Node process on port 6000 (pid 16563)
3. Did NOT kill ControlCenter (macOS system service)

Result after fix:
- Server successfully running on port 4000: http://localhost:4000/graphql

