ERROR #5 - createEvent: Non-nullable Event.creator Returns Null
================================================================================

Observed behavior:
- GraphQL mutation createEvent failed with:
  "Cannot return null for non-nullable field Event.creator."
  path: ["createEvent", "creator"]

Root causes:
1. createEvent resolver did NOT populate creator reference after saving
   - Schema defines creator: User! (non-nullable Mongoose reference)
   - Resolver returned event without calling .populate('creator')

2. Context setup missing await on User.findById()
   - context.user was a Promise instead of actual user object
   - Auth check always failed because Promise is truthy

Solution:
1. Added await event.populate('creator') after event.save()
2. Added await to User.findById() in context setup

Result after fix:
- createEvent returns event with fully populated creator User object

