SUMMARY OF FIXES APPLIED
================================================================================

1. MongoDB Atlas:
   - Whitelist your IP in Network Access
   - Remove tls: true from mongoose.connect()

2. Module paths:
   - Use correct pluralization: '../models/events' not '../models/event'

3. Port conflicts:
   - Stop stale Node processes before restarting
   - Use `lsof -nP -iTCP:PORT -sTCP:LISTEN` to find blockers
   - Keep PORT=4000 (safe default)

4. Authentication & Context:
   - Add await to all async operations (User.findById())
   - Populate Mongoose references before returning

5. Schema & Resolver alignment:
   - Make fields nullable if old data lacks values
   - Use .toObject() instead of ._doc to preserve populated refs
   - Always populate required references in resolvers

6. Development workflow:
   - Use npm run dev (nodemon) for auto-restart on file changes
   - Use npm start for production (plain node)
   - Kill old processes with: pkill -f "nodemon index.js" || pkill -f "node index.js"

