ERROR #8 - deleteEvent: Required Variable $eventId Not Provided
================================================================================

Observed behavior:
- GraphQL mutation deleteEvent returned error:
  "Variable \"$eventId\" of required type \"ID!\" was not provided."
  code: "BAD_USER_INPUT"

Root cause:
- Client called deleteEvent mutation WITHOUT providing the required $eventId variable
- Schema defines deleteEvent(eventId: ID!): [Event] - the ID! is required
- GraphQL validation failed before resolver was even called

This is NOT a server code issue - it's a client usage issue.

Correct usage:
mutation DeleteEvent($eventId: ID!) {
  deleteEvent(eventId: $eventId) {
    _id
    title
    creator {
      _id
      username
    }
  }
}

With variables:
{
  "eventId": "6a05f2bdae323154925bf36b"
}

Result after providing eventId:
- deleteEvent succeeds and returns all remaining events
